  <div id="sharePlus"><style>.cls-1 { font-size:45px; fill:#fff; }</style><text class="cls-1">+</text></div>
  </a>
  </li>
  
</ul>


    
    
    <div class="article-byline">
        <section class="article-authors">
            <div class="author-byline-images"><a href="https://in.ign.com/u/vaspaan"><img class="roundendimg" src="/s/ign/logo_ign.png" alt="Vaspaan Dastoor"></a></div><span class="by-reviewer">by</span><span class="reviewer hcard"><a class="url" href="https://in.ign.com/u/vaspaan">Vaspaan Dastoor</a></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;
        </section>
        
        <div class="article-publish-date">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="ign-icon icon-articles" width="24" height="24" viewBox="8 3 16 26"><g class="has-stroke" stroke="#838383" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 14h4m-4 4h7m-7 4h4m9-10.786V25a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H9a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V7a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10.552a2 2 0 0 1 1.548.734l3.448 4.213A2 2 0 0 1 25 11.214z"></path><path d="M19.5 5v4a2 2 0 0 0 2 2H25"></path></g></svg>
            &nbsp;<span>Posted Aug. 13, 2020, 3:19 p.m.</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section class="side-by-side article-content">
      <article class="article-section article-page">
        
        <div id="id_text">
        <p>Remedy and 505 Games have announced that Control will finally be coming to Steam, via the Control Ultimate Edition.</p>

<p>The Ultimate Edition will feature the base game and all announced DLC’s including the recently announced AWE expansion. The Ultimate Edition will launch on August 27, and cost $29.99 (approx. Rs. 2,244.65). Players who buy this edition on PS4 and Xbox One will get a free next-get upgrade as well.</p><div class="mobileArticleAds mrec1"><div class="zad halfpage" data-zadtype="halfpage" data-suffix="mrec1"></div></div></p>

<div class="vplayer"><iframe allowautoplay="" allowfullscreen="true" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/pFGgEoIVi7A" framborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></div>

<p>Furthermore, Remedy Entertainment has announced a Twitch live stream for tonight. Creative Director, Sam Lake, and Control Game Director, Mikael Kasurinenedy, will take viewers through the first 15 minutes of Control’s AWE expansion.</p>

<p>This expansion will give us the highly anticipated crossover between Control and Remedy’s previous game, Alan Wake. AWE will follow Director Jesse Faden as she makes her way through the Investigations Sector, and investigates AWE events that occurred in Bright Falls, the town in which Alan Wake was based. Remedy is also working on another game in this shared universe.</p>
        
        </div>
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
    </article>

    <div class="right-rail">
      
      
      <div class="ad-wrapper pgQSsticky">
